1
00:00:16,380 --> 00:00:17,980
(Surgery in Progress)

2
00:00:21,420 --> 00:00:22,900
(Surgery in Progress)

3
00:00:26,840 --> 00:00:27,720
How is he?

4
00:00:28,120 --> 00:00:29,360
The kid's stable for now,

5
00:00:29,360 --> 00:00:30,432
but he's still unconscious.

6
00:00:30,440 --> 00:00:31,890
We'll have to wait until he wakes up.

7
00:00:31,900 --> 00:00:34,720
=Cases Between Us=

8
00:00:34,720 --> 00:00:35,720
Hang in there.

9
00:00:36,360 --> 00:00:37,640
=Episode 8=
My poor grandson.

10
00:00:37,920 --> 00:00:40,040
That watchman

11
00:00:40,040 --> 00:00:41,240
has to pay for this.

12
00:00:41,920 --> 00:00:43,320
What about you, nephew?

13
00:00:43,880 --> 00:00:45,640
What do you mean by that?

14
00:00:45,640 --> 00:00:47,840
All the kidnapped kids
ate the steamed buns and candy.

15
00:00:48,200 --> 00:00:49,680
Why was Ai the only one who collapsed?

16
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:50,800
You're asking me?

17
00:00:51,480 --> 00:00:53,640
You're the police consultant.

18
00:00:53,880 --> 00:00:55,080
Ask them.

19
00:00:55,080 --> 00:00:56,480
Ai has diabetes,

20
00:00:57,040 --> 00:00:57,800
doesn't he?

21
00:01:00,200 --> 00:01:01,520
Diabetes.

22
00:01:01,520 --> 00:01:02,896
He went into diabetic ketoacidosis

23
00:01:02,960 --> 00:01:05,380
after eating too much sugar,
which caused him to go into shock.

24
00:01:05,480 --> 00:01:06,040
Exactly.

25
00:01:06,040 --> 00:01:06,720
Everything fits.

26
00:01:08,240 --> 00:01:10,200
I... I don't know
what you're talking about.

27
00:01:10,200 --> 00:01:11,080
Still pretending?

28
00:01:11,696 --> 00:01:13,080
The day at the police station,

29
00:01:13,080 --> 00:01:14,960
we found insulin in your bag.

30
00:01:16,340 --> 00:01:17,140
(Insulin)

31
00:01:20,144 --> 00:01:22,780
(Peking Union Medical Prescription)
The prescription was in your name.

32
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:24,920
Diabetes can skip a generation.

33
00:01:25,040 --> 00:01:26,720
Ai fainted

34
00:01:26,720 --> 00:01:27,840
because he has diabetes, too.

35
00:01:27,840 --> 00:01:28,480
You knew

36
00:01:28,480 --> 00:01:29,720
that old man didn't poison Ai.

37
00:01:29,720 --> 00:01:30,960
Why did you cover it up?

38
00:01:31,360 --> 00:01:32,280
Unless you are

39
00:01:32,840 --> 00:01:34,280
hiding something bigger.

40
00:01:35,760 --> 00:01:36,360
Me?

41
00:01:38,320 --> 00:01:39,880
What could I possibly be hiding?

42
00:01:39,880 --> 00:01:42,320
Those rickshaw pullers
kidnapped my grandson.

43
00:01:42,320 --> 00:01:44,040
They should pay for it.

44
00:01:44,680 --> 00:01:46,520
The kidnappers were rickshaw pullers.

45
00:01:46,840 --> 00:01:48,720
Last night, we also arrested

46
00:01:48,720 --> 00:01:51,040
the rickshaw boss
behind them, Zhang San.

47
00:01:56,480 --> 00:01:57,120
Stay still.

48
00:01:58,480 --> 00:01:59,240
Who are you?

49
00:01:59,240 --> 00:02:00,000
Zhang San,

50
00:02:00,080 --> 00:02:04,040
you're under arrest for arson,
kidnapping, and child trafficking.

51
00:02:04,432 --> 00:02:06,800
But whether Zhang San
was taking orders from someone else,

52
00:02:07,600 --> 00:02:08,640
that's another story.

53
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:10,320
Seventh Uncle.

54
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:12,240
Seventh Uncle,

55
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:14,560
you can't solve cases
based on guesswork.

56
00:02:15,040 --> 00:02:16,240
I never said it was you.

57
00:02:16,480 --> 00:02:17,480
Why are you so nervous?

58
00:02:17,480 --> 00:02:17,880
I...

59
00:02:17,880 --> 00:02:18,920
Let's talk somewhere else.

60
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:21,520
You can't arrest me

61
00:02:21,520 --> 00:02:23,080
without evidence.

62
00:02:23,420 --> 00:02:25,000
(Interrogation Room)

63
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:25,960
Nephew,

64
00:02:26,840 --> 00:02:27,760
here's my advice.

65
00:02:27,960 --> 00:02:28,880
Come clean.

66
00:02:29,160 --> 00:02:30,520
We're family, after all.

67
00:02:31,160 --> 00:02:32,480
Chief Yuan

68
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:33,760
isn't gentle when he investigates.

69
00:02:34,200 --> 00:02:35,240
If he

70
00:02:35,240 --> 00:02:36,360
gets upset later,

71
00:02:36,640 --> 00:02:38,080
I won't be able to help you.

72
00:02:38,240 --> 00:02:39,200
Confess to what?

73
00:02:39,720 --> 00:02:42,040
How could I possibly kidnap
my own grandson?

74
00:02:42,600 --> 00:02:43,960
That doesn't make any sense.

75
00:02:43,960 --> 00:02:46,160
The tram project
had been stalled for over six months.

76
00:02:46,496 --> 00:02:49,280
The students claimed demolishing
those pailou to build the tram lines

77
00:02:49,296 --> 00:02:50,800
would destroy cultural heritage,

78
00:02:51,040 --> 00:02:52,440
so they kept protesting.

79
00:02:53,120 --> 00:02:54,800
The rickshaw pullers believed

80
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:56,400
once the trams started running,

81
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:57,520
they'd lose their livelihoods.

82
00:02:58,040 --> 00:02:59,320
So they did everything they could

83
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:00,800
to sabotage the project.

84
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:02,080
That's exactly why

85
00:03:02,080 --> 00:03:03,040
the rickshaw pullers

86
00:03:03,040 --> 00:03:04,920
had the perfect motive
to kidnap my grandson.

87
00:03:06,080 --> 00:03:06,960
Those students

88
00:03:06,960 --> 00:03:09,040
were too idealistic
to be bought with money.

89
00:03:09,040 --> 00:03:10,752
But the rickshaw pullers
were another story.

90
00:03:10,760 --> 00:03:12,000
Bribe the rickshaw boss,

91
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:14,320
and then stage
the "Nezha burns people" act.

92
00:03:14,992 --> 00:03:16,816
Once the rumor
that tearing down those pailou

93
00:03:16,832 --> 00:03:17,880
ruined Beijing's feng shui

94
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:19,710
spread like wildfire
and panic swept the city,

95
00:03:19,720 --> 00:03:21,470
the police would arrest
the rickshaw pullers.

96
00:03:21,480 --> 00:03:22,592
The children would be found unharmed,

97
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:24,450
and the rickshaw pullers
would take the blame.

98
00:03:24,464 --> 00:03:26,190
The protesting students
would be dealt with,

99
00:03:26,208 --> 00:03:28,992
the blame would be pinned on
the pullers, public opinion would

100
00:03:29,488 --> 00:03:30,640
die down, and the tram project

101
00:03:30,640 --> 00:03:32,480
could move ahead without a hitch.

102
00:03:33,440 --> 00:03:35,560
That's all just speculation.

103
00:03:35,560 --> 00:03:37,600
The night Nezha was burning people,

104
00:03:37,760 --> 00:03:38,560
there were witnesses

105
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:41,000
all over Beijing.

106
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:43,280
They all saw the Fire Wheels
pass through a person

107
00:03:43,280 --> 00:03:44,560
and burn them to ashes.

108
00:03:44,760 --> 00:03:47,240
How could I possibly fake
something like that?

109
00:03:48,440 --> 00:03:49,400
Nephew,

110
00:03:49,640 --> 00:03:50,360
come on.

111
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:51,760
That little trick of yours.

112
00:03:51,760 --> 00:03:53,520
Don't embarrass yourself.

113
00:03:53,840 --> 00:03:56,280
Under the cover of darkness,
when no one could make out faces,

114
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:58,440
you hung something
that looked like a person

115
00:03:58,960 --> 00:04:00,120
from the pailou,

116
00:04:00,120 --> 00:04:00,960
then stationed one man

117
00:04:01,040 --> 00:04:02,920
on each side,

118
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:04,480
hidden behind the pailou.

119
00:04:04,640 --> 00:04:07,200
They wrapped cotton around a wheel,

120
00:04:07,200 --> 00:04:08,120
set it on fire,

121
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:09,360
and hoisted it into the air.

122
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:10,480
As the cotton burned,

123
00:04:10,480 --> 00:04:11,600
the flames flickered,

124
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:14,520
making it sway and dart through the air.

125
00:04:14,760 --> 00:04:15,680
That's why it looked

126
00:04:15,680 --> 00:04:17,480
like Nezha's Fire Wheels
were burning people.

127
00:04:21,440 --> 00:04:24,520
So check the cartwheels
under Zhang San's supervision

128
00:04:24,520 --> 00:04:25,760
for burn marks.

129
00:04:27,560 --> 00:04:28,800
There's your evidence.

130
00:04:38,752 --> 00:04:39,680
If that's the case,

131
00:04:39,680 --> 00:04:41,000
why don't you think

132
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:42,680
Zhang San kidnapped the children?

133
00:04:42,680 --> 00:04:44,920
So he could force me
to stop the project?

134
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:46,520
There were over a dozen children.

135
00:04:46,520 --> 00:04:48,040
If he meant to use them
as leverage,

136
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:50,600
he wouldn't have left them
unharmed in that shed all night.

137
00:04:50,608 --> 00:04:52,400
Even the people whom he burned
at the pailou

138
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:53,400
were fake.

139
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:55,080
Nephew,

140
00:04:56,080 --> 00:04:56,920
if you were going to

141
00:04:58,440 --> 00:04:59,680
kidnap someone,

142
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:01,200
why did you have to steal a monkey?

143
00:05:06,360 --> 00:05:08,440
That monkey sheds more hair than you do.

144
00:05:14,080 --> 00:05:15,680
You're making accusations without proof.

145
00:05:15,712 --> 00:05:16,920
I don't know this Zhang San.

146
00:05:17,160 --> 00:05:19,040
How could I have ordered him
to do anything?

147
00:05:22,880 --> 00:05:23,800
That's true.

148
00:05:24,280 --> 00:05:24,880
At first,

149
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:26,280
we didn't have any evidence.

150
00:05:26,520 --> 00:05:28,400
And Zhang San was loyal.

151
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:29,560
He took

152
00:05:29,560 --> 00:05:30,840
all the blame himself.

153
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:31,920
But...

154
00:05:32,760 --> 00:05:35,040
your mistake was
being a little too generous.

155
00:05:35,280 --> 00:05:36,240
Why did you buy him

156
00:05:36,240 --> 00:05:38,280
a watch?

157
00:05:44,360 --> 00:05:46,640
The latest Patek Philippe.

158
00:05:47,080 --> 00:05:49,160
He's just a rickshaw puller
who can't even read.

159
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:51,088
How could he possibly afford something
like that?

160
00:05:51,104 --> 00:05:54,160
Uh, a watch proves nothing.

161
00:05:54,880 --> 00:05:56,360
Who saw me give it to him?

162
00:05:56,360 --> 00:05:57,920
Are you dumb, or am I?

163
00:05:58,560 --> 00:05:59,600
Every Patek Philippe

164
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:00,610
has its own serial number.

165
00:06:00,620 --> 00:06:02,860
Check with the manufacturer,
and you'll know who bought it.

166
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:05,840
Just a reminder.

167
00:06:06,080 --> 00:06:06,880
My sister

168
00:06:06,880 --> 00:06:08,640
is one of Patek Philippe's top clients.

169
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:11,920
Want me to have someone look it up?

170
00:06:14,120 --> 00:06:14,800
Seventh Uncle...

171
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:25,880
Seventh Uncle.

172
00:06:29,560 --> 00:06:31,000
You've got a big family business.

173
00:06:32,120 --> 00:06:33,600
How could you understand

174
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:36,240
what it's like for a small business
like ours?

175
00:06:37,320 --> 00:06:38,280
These past few years,

176
00:06:39,080 --> 00:06:40,160
the tram company

177
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:43,920
has drained us dry.

178
00:06:45,296 --> 00:06:46,960
The pressure from above
keeps mounting.

179
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:49,560
The project was already
hard enough to push through,

180
00:06:50,880 --> 00:06:52,720
and then the students
started protesting.

181
00:06:54,320 --> 00:06:55,320
Who would've thought

182
00:06:56,624 --> 00:06:58,160
that we lost everything in the end?

183
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:01,120
I...

184
00:07:01,880 --> 00:07:03,960
I almost lost my grandson, too.

185
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:23,760
My nephew, well...

186
00:07:24,740 --> 00:07:28,700
(Jingshi Police Department)

187
00:07:30,160 --> 00:07:31,320
The boy is the family's

188
00:07:31,320 --> 00:07:32,600
only grandson.

189
00:07:32,920 --> 00:07:35,120
They've spoiled him so much
that they'd rather carry him

190
00:07:35,760 --> 00:07:37,040
than let him walk.

191
00:07:37,640 --> 00:07:38,680
And now,

192
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:40,680
he's using his own grandson

193
00:07:40,680 --> 00:07:41,520
as a bargaining chip.

194
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:43,632
What a world. It's turning people

195
00:07:43,632 --> 00:07:45,080
into something less than human.

196
00:07:47,040 --> 00:07:47,720
What's that?

197
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:48,720
You eat it all the time.

198
00:07:56,480 --> 00:07:57,360
Malt candy.

199
00:07:57,600 --> 00:07:59,200
Don't you ever get sick of it?

200
00:08:10,400 --> 00:08:10,920
Young Master.

201
00:08:11,720 --> 00:08:12,360
Perfect timing.

202
00:08:13,320 --> 00:08:13,800
Come.

203
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:14,560
Take these.

204
00:08:18,760 --> 00:08:20,200
The article Mr. Shao polished for us

205
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:21,240
is almost done.

206
00:08:21,440 --> 00:08:22,880
I've waited over half a month.

207
00:08:22,880 --> 00:08:25,200
It deserves a front-page extra tomorrow.

208
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:27,760
Will they agree to print it?

209
00:08:29,360 --> 00:08:31,240
I slipped the editor a red packet.

210
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:33,560
I'll cover all the printing costs.

211
00:08:34,016 --> 00:08:35,560
All they need to do is distribute it.

212
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:37,600
Let's see which little scoundrel

213
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:39,040
tries to steal my thunder this time.

214
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:40,480
Say, Young Master.

215
00:08:40,760 --> 00:08:41,640
Chief Yuan's here.

216
00:08:41,800 --> 00:08:42,920
Is he? What's he here for?

217
00:08:42,976 --> 00:08:44,832
He's here to bring a gun
to the Young Lady.

218
00:08:47,440 --> 00:08:48,920
He's really keeping his word.

219
00:08:48,920 --> 00:08:49,400
Let's go

220
00:08:49,400 --> 00:08:50,680
and see what kind of gun it is.

221
00:08:50,680 --> 00:08:51,760
He's gone.

222
00:08:52,640 --> 00:08:53,360
Gone?

223
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:54,200
Where did he go?

224
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:55,216
Madam told Chief Yuan

225
00:08:55,264 --> 00:08:56,680
to take the Young Lady out for dinner.

226
00:08:58,380 --> 00:08:59,660
My mom's playing matchmaker again.

227
00:08:59,680 --> 00:09:01,540
One's a block of wood,
the other's a firecracker.

228
00:09:01,550 --> 00:09:03,490
Put them together,
and they'll burn the house down.

229
00:09:03,500 --> 00:09:04,560
It won't be that bad.

230
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:08,520
I've heard first dates
are always awkward.

231
00:09:08,520 --> 00:09:10,320
If it's awkward,
he can make conversation.

232
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:14,920
Wait.

233
00:09:15,728 --> 00:09:17,040
Zhao Wan'er will probably end up

234
00:09:17,056 --> 00:09:18,400
using me as the topic.

235
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:19,480
Zhao Cai.

236
00:09:19,720 --> 00:09:20,760
Go see where they went.

237
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:22,440
Hurry.

238
00:09:24,060 --> 00:09:27,460
(International Hotel)

239
00:09:36,560 --> 00:09:37,960
You wrapped up the case pretty fast.

240
00:09:37,984 --> 00:09:40,080
I thank you
on behalf of the children's parents.

241
00:09:40,560 --> 00:09:42,080
Young Master Zhao helped a lot, too.

242
00:09:42,280 --> 00:09:44,600
Without him, the case wouldn't
have been solved this quickly.

243
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:46,840
Then you two should work together more.

244
00:09:48,680 --> 00:09:49,560
Well,

245
00:09:50,320 --> 00:09:51,320
it depends on fate.

246
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:53,840
The world's vast.

247
00:09:53,840 --> 00:09:55,400
Meeting someone at all is fate enough.

248
00:09:55,920 --> 00:09:57,040
To fate. Cheers.

249
00:09:57,400 --> 00:09:58,120
Cheers.

250
00:10:02,032 --> 00:10:02,920
What's wrong with you?

251
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:05,120
I'm so sorry.

252
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:09,120
I heard

253
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:11,320
you used to study
at a military academy in Britain.

254
00:10:12,440 --> 00:10:13,200
Three years.

255
00:10:20,760 --> 00:10:22,240
Don't be so nervous.

256
00:10:22,680 --> 00:10:24,160
That's just how my mom is.

257
00:10:24,320 --> 00:10:26,048
Whenever she sees a promising young man,

258
00:10:26,048 --> 00:10:27,200
she wants to bring him home.

259
00:10:27,520 --> 00:10:28,720
She likes you.

260
00:10:28,784 --> 00:10:30,320
She's mentioned you more than once.

261
00:10:30,560 --> 00:10:32,280
Tonight's dinner is
just to keep her happy.

262
00:10:33,776 --> 00:10:35,360
Not many wealthy families in Beijing

263
00:10:35,560 --> 00:10:37,480
are as lively and close-knit

264
00:10:37,480 --> 00:10:38,040
as yours.

265
00:10:38,040 --> 00:10:38,560
Of course.

266
00:10:38,560 --> 00:10:39,680
How else could we have raised

267
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:41,072
a troublemaker like Zhao Shaoshang?

268
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:51,640
That interruption
made me forget something important.

269
00:10:57,800 --> 00:10:59,240
You said that.

270
00:10:59,760 --> 00:11:01,240
Just you wait.

271
00:11:01,248 --> 00:11:02,360
Just wait till I get back...

272
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:05,400
Are you blind?

273
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:08,920
Jeez.

274
00:11:12,840 --> 00:11:13,960
You?

275
00:11:16,680 --> 00:11:17,400
Young Master Zhao.

276
00:11:26,800 --> 00:11:27,640
I'll go check on him.

277
00:11:39,580 --> 00:11:40,580
(International Hotel)

278
00:11:42,040 --> 00:11:43,080
What are you doing here?

279
00:11:44,608 --> 00:11:45,800
You've got the wrong person.

280
00:11:47,360 --> 00:11:48,240
Zhao Shaoshang.

281
00:11:48,400 --> 00:11:49,320
You're following me.

282
00:11:49,320 --> 00:11:50,120
Don't be ridiculous!

283
00:11:50,520 --> 00:11:51,720
Don't make things up.

284
00:11:52,440 --> 00:11:53,520
Then what are you doing here?

285
00:11:54,040 --> 00:11:55,000
Working part-time?

286
00:11:57,400 --> 00:11:59,720
I'm working part-time to pay my tuition.
Is that wrong?

287
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:01,440
You're working to pay your tuition?

288
00:12:03,120 --> 00:12:05,360
You're worried about your sister,
aren't you?

289
00:12:06,144 --> 00:12:07,560
Afraid I'd give her a hard time?

290
00:12:11,320 --> 00:12:12,680
You know what my sister's like.

291
00:12:12,680 --> 00:12:14,360
She blows up at the slightest thing.

292
00:12:15,160 --> 00:12:16,560
Also, you never mince words.

293
00:12:16,592 --> 00:12:18,240
If you two ended up fighting
over dinner,

294
00:12:18,272 --> 00:12:19,232
it wouldn't be worth it.

295
00:12:19,264 --> 00:12:20,370
I don't think that'll happen.

296
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:21,680
Your sister's great.

297
00:12:21,680 --> 00:12:22,560
She's funny

298
00:12:22,560 --> 00:12:23,400
and considerate.

299
00:12:23,640 --> 00:12:24,440
Way better than you.

300
00:12:28,760 --> 00:12:29,640
You like her?

301
00:12:35,720 --> 00:12:36,320
Good.

302
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:38,040
That's good.

303
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:40,240
You can ask her out more often.

304
00:12:40,240 --> 00:12:40,880
Well,

305
00:12:40,880 --> 00:12:42,640
you two would actually
make a good match.

306
00:12:43,120 --> 00:12:44,120
She's single now.

307
00:12:44,160 --> 00:12:45,470
I'll keep you supplied with wine,

308
00:12:45,480 --> 00:12:46,720
and then we'll be family.

309
00:12:51,740 --> 00:12:55,280
(International Hotel)

310
00:12:55,280 --> 00:12:56,120
Have you eaten?

311
00:12:56,480 --> 00:12:57,120
No.

312
00:12:57,560 --> 00:12:57,960
Let's go.

313
00:12:58,200 --> 00:12:59,320
Didn't you just eat?

314
00:13:00,080 --> 00:13:01,360
I hate Western food.

315
00:13:07,088 --> 00:13:09,232
Then you and Wan'er
definitely won't get along.

316
00:13:09,280 --> 00:13:13,280
(International Hotel)

317
00:13:13,280 --> 00:13:14,000
Wait up.

318
00:13:16,768 --> 00:13:18,040
(Noodle House)
Here you go.

319
00:13:18,040 --> 00:13:18,640
Thanks.

320
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:24,120
This place is the real deal.

321
00:13:24,120 --> 00:13:24,640
Come on.

322
00:13:28,280 --> 00:13:29,296
(Notice: Newlywed joy! Back home)
Wedding.

323
00:13:29,300 --> 00:13:30,160
(for a wedding banquet. Closed.)

324
00:13:31,960 --> 00:13:32,520
Well,

325
00:13:33,160 --> 00:13:34,240
looks like you're in luck.

326
00:13:34,496 --> 00:13:35,880
You get to taste my cooking today.

327
00:14:25,160 --> 00:14:25,800
Give it a smell.

328
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:47,200
How is it?

329
00:14:47,920 --> 00:14:48,480
It's good.

330
00:14:49,120 --> 00:14:51,800
I didn't expect a rich young master
like you to know how to cook.

331
00:14:52,672 --> 00:14:54,680
Whatever you get into,
you should do it well.

332
00:14:54,848 --> 00:14:56,680
If you want to be a true foodie
in Beijing,

333
00:14:56,680 --> 00:14:57,920
you'd better know how to cook.

334
00:14:57,952 --> 00:14:59,536
Zhajiangmian is just beginner level.

335
00:14:59,552 --> 00:15:01,152
Next time I'll make you
braised scallions.

336
00:15:01,280 --> 00:15:02,840
Made with the finest Shandong scallions,

337
00:15:02,896 --> 00:15:05,280
braised until they're soft
and golden. That's my secret recipe.

338
00:15:06,352 --> 00:15:08,470
A chef once offered me
ten gold bars for the recipe,

339
00:15:08,480 --> 00:15:09,480
and I wouldn't teach him.

340
00:15:12,064 --> 00:15:14,040
What are you laughing at?
Don't believe me?

341
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:15,520
Listen.

342
00:15:16,440 --> 00:15:18,080
My philosophy in life is simple.

343
00:15:18,280 --> 00:15:20,048
If you're going
to have fun, do it seriously.

344
00:15:20,112 --> 00:15:21,240
Have as much fun as possible.

345
00:15:21,800 --> 00:15:23,840
Racing pigeons,
cricket fighting, or growing gourds.

346
00:15:23,840 --> 00:15:24,640
You know?

347
00:15:24,960 --> 00:15:27,160
There isn't anyone in Jingshi
who can outplay me.

348
00:15:28,080 --> 00:15:29,120
I'm laughing because

349
00:15:29,920 --> 00:15:30,760
everyone says

350
00:15:30,760 --> 00:15:33,520
you're a spoiled rich brat.

351
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:35,160
But from what I've seen,

352
00:15:35,712 --> 00:15:36,816
you're actually very serious

353
00:15:37,600 --> 00:15:38,480
and very focused.

354
00:15:39,280 --> 00:15:40,400
It's just that

355
00:15:40,720 --> 00:15:41,920
people have to know you well

356
00:15:42,960 --> 00:15:44,400
before they see who you really are.

357
00:15:57,200 --> 00:15:58,320
It's just having fun.

358
00:15:58,560 --> 00:15:59,600
You make it sound

359
00:16:01,360 --> 00:16:02,080
like I've done

360
00:16:02,080 --> 00:16:03,280
something extraordinary.

361
00:16:04,720 --> 00:16:05,600
You have.

362
00:16:17,200 --> 00:16:18,160
You have a cat?

363
00:16:21,080 --> 00:16:22,080
It's cute.

364
00:16:23,360 --> 00:16:24,160
It's a stray.

365
00:16:25,360 --> 00:16:26,360
I don't keep pets.

366
00:16:27,400 --> 00:16:28,280
You don't like animals?

367
00:16:29,856 --> 00:16:31,680
I don't want anything
weighing on my mind.

368
00:16:32,144 --> 00:16:33,360
If it wants to come, it'll come.

369
00:16:33,360 --> 00:16:34,360
If it doesn't,

370
00:16:34,960 --> 00:16:36,160
I won't lose sleep over it.

371
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:46,760
Is that yesterday's mooncake?

372
00:16:48,720 --> 00:16:49,800
Yang Dezhi brought it over.

373
00:16:49,800 --> 00:16:50,912
I don't celebrate festivals.

374
00:16:51,008 --> 00:16:52,640
You don't? Why not?

375
00:16:54,360 --> 00:16:55,760
During my three years in Britain,

376
00:16:55,760 --> 00:16:57,680
they celebrate their holidays,

377
00:16:57,680 --> 00:16:58,720
not Chinese festivals.

378
00:16:59,260 --> 00:17:00,544
After I came back, it was just me.

379
00:17:00,560 --> 00:17:02,450
Didn't feel like
there was anything to celebrate.

380
00:17:02,920 --> 00:17:04,520
Now I've got to say something.

381
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:06,360
For us Chinese,

382
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:08,240
festivals are about remembering

383
00:17:09,744 --> 00:17:11,392
and having something to look forward to.

384
00:17:21,408 --> 00:17:22,976
This year, I'll celebrate with you.

385
00:17:23,024 --> 00:17:23,840
From now on,

386
00:17:24,840 --> 00:17:28,352
Mid-Autumn, Spring Festival,
Lantern Festival, Dragon Boat Festival,

387
00:17:28,400 --> 00:17:30,120
if you've got no one
to spend them with,

388
00:17:30,120 --> 00:17:31,040
just call me.

389
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:34,160
Mid-Autumn was yesterday.

390
00:17:34,160 --> 00:17:35,040
It's over.

391
00:17:35,480 --> 00:17:36,200
Look.

392
00:17:37,040 --> 00:17:39,360
The moon is fuller on the sixteenth.

393
00:17:41,280 --> 00:17:42,160
Let's enjoy it.

394
00:17:48,720 --> 00:17:49,360
Too sweet.

395
00:17:49,360 --> 00:17:50,840
How can you love sweets this much?

396
00:17:53,560 --> 00:17:54,320
Pretty good, huh?

397
00:17:54,560 --> 00:17:55,720
You missed it?

398
00:17:57,240 --> 00:17:57,560
Watch.

399
00:17:57,560 --> 00:17:58,360
I'll do it again.

400
00:17:59,680 --> 00:18:00,440
See?

401
00:18:00,440 --> 00:18:02,360
I missed it because you were watching.

402
00:18:02,600 --> 00:18:03,560
One more time.

403
00:18:04,720 --> 00:18:05,440
Isn't it good?

404
00:18:05,840 --> 00:18:06,560
Yeah.

405
00:18:08,170 --> 00:18:09,728
I get carried away now. One more time.

406
00:18:09,840 --> 00:18:10,560
See?

407
00:18:11,120 --> 00:18:12,240
Nice shot.

408
00:18:15,500 --> 00:18:18,660
(End of Episode 8)

409
00:18:19,400 --> 00:18:21,040
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

410
00:18:21,040 --> 00:18:22,580
♪Troubled times
are but a laughing matter♪

411
00:18:22,580 --> 00:18:23,830
♪However, the world changes♪

412
00:18:23,830 --> 00:18:25,750
♪You'll still be by my side♪

413
00:18:25,750 --> 00:18:27,440
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

414
00:18:27,440 --> 00:18:29,010
♪Praise and blame come and go♪

415
00:18:29,010 --> 00:18:30,580
♪If this is my final chapter♪

416
00:18:30,580 --> 00:18:33,080
♪I'll solve this mystery with you♪
